text: Chester House, 2016 Chester House is a Grade II listed house on the west side of Wimbledon Common, Wimbledon, London, built in about 1700 or earlier. The radical politician and reformer John Horne Tooke lived there from 1792 until his death in 1812. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Grade II listed buildings in the London Borough of Merton Category:Houses completed in 1700 Category:Houses in the London Borough of Merton Category:1700 establishments in England Category:Grade II listed houses in London
